    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "Air Mail\nJUL S\n5\nPM\n1930\nTEN\nUSROSTAGE\nIN. ABRREGISTO UF\nPILOT W D.ATOR\nC. A. M. 30\nJUNE ISTH - 21ST.\nINTERSTATE AIRLINES, INC.\nCHICAGO - - ATLANTA\nDae lUn Weck\n210) -N- \u003e54st\nleveland his",
      "1999.023.004 a",
      "M. D. \"DoC\" ATOR, night mail pilot for Interstate\nAirlines, Inc., on the northern route between Chicago\nand Evansville, Ind., connecting at Evansville with the\nSt. Louis and Atlanta mail planes, learned to fly at\nJacksonville, Ill, his home town. For two years after-\nwards he barnstormed about the country gaining experi\nence, and in the Spring of 1927, took charge of a field\nat Champaign, Ill. During this time he did some fly-\ning for representatives of Prairie Farmer magazine, and\nin the Fall of 1928 flew for John Livingston of the\nMidwest Hirways, Inc. On December 1, 1928, Pilot Ator accepted a\nposition with Interstate Airlines, Inc., to fly the airmail, and has for the\nmost part flown the route between\nChicago and Evansville. He\nresides in Chicago, Ill.\n\"oc\" Ator"
    ],
